Reasoning: The paper deals with combinatorial properties of repetitions in formal words, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). It also involves the study of algorithms for identifying and classifying these repetitions, which falls under the category of formal languages (cs.FL). Information theory (cs.IT) is also relevant as the paper discusses the compression of words by exploiting the properties of maximal repetitions. The paper also involves the analysis of the structure of words, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS).
